Am Dienstag, den 15.05.2007, 14:03 +0200 schrieb Gabriel Kerneis:
> Hi everybody,
> 
> I'm trying to use ocamlfind with the new camlp4 but I can't use
> camlp4rf or camlp4of, and I can't define an alias camlp4o=camlp4of
> (whereas this is possible for ocamlc=ocamlc.opt, through findlib.conf).
> 
> Does anyone have a hint about this ? Or is it just... impossible ?

Well, findlib isn't yet ready for the new features of the _coming_,
_not_yet_released_, _still_developing_ O'Caml 3.10. If you need new
command-line features, use -pp.

It is not yet clear to me how to systematically deal with the
command-line of the new camlp4. There isn't much documentation, and I
don't want to waste time reading the sources to find it out on my own.
Maybe Nicolas can give hints what would be necessary.

Gerd
